# Task Detail View: Timeline Feature + Remove Outdated Meeting Integration

The task detail side panel ([StandupInspector.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx)) currently contains three overlapping note-taking sections that were built incrementally. Two are now outdated and superseded by the Daily Meeting Notes system. Additionally, the status history display is a minimal text list that should be a rich visual timeline.

## Proposed Changes

### StandupInspector Component

#### [MODIFY] [StandupInspector.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx)

**Remove outdated sections:**
- **Interrogation Log** (lines 494â€“529): Replaced by Daily Meeting Notes. Remove the entire section including the `logInput` state, [handleAddLog](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx#116-121), and the rendering block.
- **Standup Notes** (lines 533â€“583): Old form with free-text `blockedBy`, `reason`, `note` fields. Also superseded by Daily Meeting Notes. Remove the section, the [useNotes](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useNotes.ts#6-46) hook import, and related state (`blockedBy`, `reason`, `noteText`, [handleSave](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx#104-115)).

**Remove from props interface:**
- `interrogationLogs`, `onAddLog` â€” no longer needed

**Add rich visual timeline to replace the minimal Status History section (lines 246â€“273):**
- Vertical timeline with connector lines between status nodes
- Each node shows: timestamp, status name, person, and duration since previous status
- Color-coded severity dots (critical = red, high = amber, normal = zinc)
- Bottleneck statuses highlighted with a glow effect
- "Reprocess" entries marked with a loop icon
- Collapsible with expand/collapse toggle if there are many entries

---

